                "name": "inventor weapon innovation",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Battle-Grapple Innovation",
            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "Zovi fights using a complex device she crafted from scavenged clockwork parts and ancient Azlanti magitech. Similar in appearance to a grappling hook attached to an auto-retracting cable, this device is called a battle-grapple innovation. It allows Zovi to use her Magitech Propulsion and Whirling Flurry abilities. Unlike other tethered weapons, each time Zovi uses her battle-grapple innovation, she automatically retrieves it as a free action, allowing her to make multiple attacks in a row. It otherwise functions as an inventor weapon innovation with no modifications.",
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
          "name": "Battle-Grapple Innovation",
          "offensive_action_type": "ability",
          "subtype": "offensive_action",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability": {
            "ability_type": "offensive",
            "action_type": {
              "name": "One Action",
              "subtype": "action_type",
              "type": "stat_block_section"
            },
            "effect": "The dero excises damaged flesh and crudely stitches wounds shut, healing themself or an ally in reach for 2d8+14 Hit Points. For 1 hour, the target has slashing weakness 2 and is immune to Dero Medicine.",
            "name": "Dero Medicine",
            "requirement": "The dero is wearing a cytillesh toolkit and has a hand free",
            "subtype": "ability",
            "traits": [
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 89,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "46d51374c2ada72347818dbac1edd7a3",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Healing",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
